{"version":"NotebookV1","origId":1083584440950732,"name":"10-2 Linear Regression","language":"python","commands":[{"version":"CommandV1","origId":1083584440950733,"guid":"66555e15-28e3-450e-9619-e0d6917066ad","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":1.0,"command":"\n%md\n# Regression: Predicting Rental Price\n\nIn this notebook, we will use the dataset we cleansed in the previous lab to predict Airbnb rental prices in San Francisco.","commandVersion":0,"state":"error","results":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultSubCmdIds":[],"tableResultIndex":null,"nuid":"cbab0fee-c381-49b6-bd5f-ec29a75748bb"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":1083584440950734,"guid":"254621ef-af8b-4a40-8948-2d501f615b2e","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":2.0,"command":"filePath = \"/databricks-datasets/learning-spark-v2/sf-airbnb/sf-airbnb-clean.parquet\"\nairbnbDF = spark.read.parquet(filePath)\ndisplay(airbnbDF)","commandVersion":0,"state":"error","results":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"5467","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultSubCmdIds":[],"tableResultIndex":null,"nuid":"9326f36b-cd05-4f25-9fc5-942786e1801e"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":1083584440950735,"guid":"ed4d958d-cda6-42eb-a799-f7364b0dbdb9","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":3.0,"command":"%md\n## Train/Test Split\n\nWhen we are building ML models, we don't want to look at our test data (why is that?). \n\nLet's keep 80% for the training set and set aside 20% of our data for the test set. We will use the `randomSplit` method [Python](https://spark.apache.org/docs/latest/api/python/pyspark.sql.html#pyspark.sql.DataFrame.randomSplit)/[Scala](https://spark.apache.org/docs/latest/api/scala/#org.apache.spark.sql.Dataset).\n\n**Question**: Why is it necessary to set a seed?","commandVersion":0,"state":"error","results":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultSubCmdIds":[],"tableResultIndex":null,"nuid":"a751bdbb-7122-40e7-83f5-10235e0793b3"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":1083584440950736,"guid":"52586724-5a51-44fc-a936-dceb18914bd9","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":4.0,"command":"trainDF, testDF = airbnbDF.randomSplit([.8, .2], seed=42)\nprint(f\"There are {trainDF.cache().count()} rows in the training set, and {testDF.cache().count()} in the test set\")","commandVersion":0,"state":"error","results":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultSubCmdIds":[],"tableResultIndex":null,"nuid":"7cfe04ac-f148-403e-8d9c-8693517939b4"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":1083584440950737,"guid":"f00b8ef7-34a8-410e-896c-a7bbf558f29d","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":5.0,"command":"%md\n\n**Question**: What happens if you change your cluster configuration?\n\nTo test this out, try spinning up a cluster with just one worker, and another with two workers. NOTE: This data is quite small (one partition), and you will need to test it out with a larger dataset (e.g. 2+ partitions) to see the difference, such as: `databricks-datasets/learning-spark-v2/sf-airbnb/sf-airbnb-clean-100p.parquet.` However, in this code below, we will simply repartition our data to simulate how it could have been partitioned differently on a different cluster configuration, and see if we get the same number of data points in our training set. ","commandVersion":0,"state":"error","results":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultSubCmdIds":[],"tableResultIndex":null,"nuid":"d01697ab-596c-426f-a64b-7f6d17119e41"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":1083584440950738,"guid":"dfb47075-ca6b-48bf-b692-7a68a3e14cc1","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":6.0,"command":"(trainRepartitionDF, testRepartitionDF) = (airbnbDF\n                                           .repartition(24)\n                                           .randomSplit([.8, .2], seed=42))\n\nprint(trainRepartitionDF.count())","commandVersion":0,"state":"error","results":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultSubCmdIds":[],"tableResultIndex":null,"nuid":"73d300c2-73e3-47d1-8e63-5201254b750d"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":1083584440950739,"guid":"a6c7eb6a-8b8d-463a-85fa-201679222b39","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":7.0,"command":"%md\nWhen you do an 80/20 train/test split, it is an \"approximate\" 80/20 split. It is not an exact 80/20 split, and when we the partitioning of our data changes, we show that we get not only a different # of data points in train/test, but also different data points.\n\nOur recommendation is to split your data once, then write it out to its own train/test folder so you don't have these reproducibility issues.","commandVersion":0,"state":"error","results":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultSubCmdIds":[],"tableResultIndex":null,"nuid":"cb9a95e3-0fc0-4e61-8d3c-e6ab5893f806"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":1083584440950740,"guid":"f7617227-e616-4256-ac66-e0b75ea98e0c","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":8.0,"command":"%md\nWe are going to build a very simple linear regression model predicting `price` just given the number of `bedrooms`.\n\n**Question**: What are some assumptions of the linear regression model?","commandVersion":0,"state":"error","results":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultSubCmdIds":[],"tableResultIndex":null,"nuid":"3571b60b-919a-415d-a051-8c2c216392ee"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":1083584440950741,"guid":"8b562baa-4459-4110-97ad-f1a2827807b9","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":9.0,"command":"display(trainDF.select(\"price\", \"bedrooms\").summary())","commandVersion":0,"state":"error","results":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"480","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultSubCmdIds":[],"tableResultIndex":null,"nuid":"8ce302ee-b462-4097-906b-a88a6bcec640"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":1083584440950742,"guid":"1b80abed-f02c-42d0-a407-d2e07c39eed8","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":10.0,"command":"%md\nThere do appear some outliers in our dataset for the price ($10,000 a night??). Just keep this in mind when we are building our models :).","commandVersion":0,"state":"error","results":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultSubCmdIds":[],"tableResultIndex":null,"nuid":"67f1f7a7-1035-4b87-b58c-33a790b86d67"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":1083584440950743,"guid":"3b491bac-73bc-4ed2-8cfb-c0a396338d39","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":11.0,"command":"%md\n## Vector Assembler\n\nLinear Regression expects a column of Vector type as input.\n\nWe can easily get the values from the `bedrooms` column into a single vector using `VectorAssembler` [Python](https://spark.apache.org/docs/latest/api/python/pyspark.ml.html#pyspark.ml.feature.VectorAssembler)/[Scala](https://spark.apache.org/docs/latest/api/scala/#org.apache.spark.ml.feature.VectorAssembler). VectorAssembler is an example of a **transformer**. Transformers take in a DataFrame, and return a new DataFrame with one or more columns appended to it. They do not learn from your data, but apply rule based transformations.","commandVersion":0,"state":"error","results":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultSubCmdIds":[],"tableResultIndex":null,"nuid":"a085bbc9-f65f-4f73-bc6d-a45a5727762e"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":1083584440950744,"guid":"ae7412e5-17aa-40a0-911a-b05cb5614e54","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":12.0,"command":"from pyspark.ml.feature import VectorAssembler\n\nvecAssembler = VectorAssembler(inputCols=[\"bedrooms\"], outputCol=\"features\")\n\nvecTrainDF = vecAssembler.transform(trainDF)\n\nvecTrainDF.select(\"bedrooms\", \"features\", \"price\").show(10)","commandVersion":0,"state":"error","results":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultSubCmdIds":[],"tableResultIndex":null,"nuid":"b48eaf92-c64c-428d-a0c6-43aa01ced58a"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":1083584440950745,"guid":"45819b3b-0f71-48e0-843b-670340f7fb1c","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":13.0,"command":"%md\n## Linear Regression\n\nNow that we have prepared our data, we can use the `LinearRegression` estimator to build our first model [Python](https://spark.apache.org/docs/latest/api/python/pyspark.ml.html#pyspark.ml.regression.LinearRegression)/[Scala](https://spark.apache.org/docs/latest/api/scala/#org.apache.spark.ml.regression.LinearRegression). Estimators accept a DataFrame as input and return a model, and have a `.fit()` method. ","commandVersion":0,"state":"error","results":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultSubCmdIds":[],"tableResultIndex":null,"nuid":"2655e5f9-b679-43d6-aaed-281d96ab7790"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":1083584440950746,"guid":"aa2c6abe-6e5e-4c9e-97d8-0641dbf64d61","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":14.0,"command":"from pyspark.ml.regression import LinearRegression\n\nlr = LinearRegression(featuresCol=\"features\", labelCol=\"price\")\nlrModel = lr.fit(vecTrainDF)","commandVersion":0,"state":"error","results":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultSubCmdIds":[],"tableResultIndex":null,"nuid":"96471504-df6c-4c88-8335-a93307622979"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":1083584440950747,"guid":"be465af2-5ff6-4058-b186-b0daf671c173","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":15.0,"command":"%md\n## Inspect the model","commandVersion":0,"state":"error","results":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultSubCmdIds":[],"tableResultIndex":null,"nuid":"b2779025-b300-4df4-814c-d8d70538bbc1"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":1083584440950748,"guid":"24f3f39e-5fca-4b2e-92d4-76a57fa7165e","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":16.0,"command":"m = round(lrModel.coefficients[0], 2)\nb = round(lrModel.intercept, 2)\n\nprint(f\"The formula for the linear regression line is price = {m}*bedrooms + {b}\")","commandVersion":0,"state":"error","results":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultSubCmdIds":[],"tableResultIndex":null,"nuid":"747818ac-bf38-4825-9f89-3f19c2c8fae3"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":1083584440950749,"guid":"b9cdcb0a-587c-4f70-9cc9-48405659e64a","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":17.0,"command":"%md\n## Pipeline","commandVersion":0,"state":"error","results":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":null,"yColumns":null,"pivotColumns":null,"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultSubCmdIds":[],"tableResultIndex":null,"nuid":"934c78c4-03bc-4ef2-a82b-36a3c491dd8d"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":1083584440950750,"guid":"8e3103fe-25e7-48ae-89b2-e33348328282","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":18.0,"command":"from pyspark.ml import Pipeline\n\npipeline = Pipeline(stages=[vecAssembler, lr])\npipelineModel = pipeline.fit(trainDF)","commandVersion":0,"state":"error","results":null,"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"co